rs11136000 | Alzheimers disease

Populations: Cases and controls

Risk allele frequency

The MAF for the first phase is reported for this SNP, but the RAF for the combined phase does not. We will consider the sample size for controls and cases from the first phase: 3941 cases and 7848 controls and the corresponding odd ratio 1/0.84 = 1.1904762. The MAF reported corresponds in the paper corresponds to the minor allele in controls, so RAF in the catalog will be preserved.

rs10520045 | Major depressive disorder

After excluding SNPs not present on the HumanHap 550v3 chip used for the control samples, the final data set comprised 491,238 autosomal markers from 597 cases and 1295 control subjects. This number of SNPs corresponds to 79% of the 620,901 SNPs genotyped per patient. The replication sample consisted of 409 inpatients (179 men, 230 women) and 541 German control subjects matched to provide an equivalent distribution of age and sex

Sensitivity - Specificity plot

curated_gwas <- subset(assoc, !is.na(CASES))

senses <- SenSes(
    curated_gwas[,c('CASES', 'CONTROLS', 'RISK.ALLELE.FREQUENCY', 'ORorBETA')]
    )

curated_gwas_senses <- cbind(curated_gwas, senses)
# plot(curated_gwas_senses$Specificity, curated_gwas_senses$Sensitivity,
#      main = "Specificity vs. Sensitivity for GWA studies",
#      xlab = "1- Specificity", ylab = "Sensitivity", xlim = c(0, 1), ylim = c(0, 1))
# text(curated_gwas_senses$Specificity, curated_gwas_senses$Sensitivity, 
#       row.names(curated_gwas_senses), cex=0.6, pos=4, col="blue")
# # text(1- curated_gwas_senses$Specificity, curated_gwas_senses$Sensitivity, 
# #      curated_gwas_senses$RISK.ALLELE.FREQUENCY, cex=0.6, pos=1, col="blue")
# abline(0, 1, col = "red", lty=2)
library('rCharts')
dP <- dPlot(
  Sensitivity ~ Specificity,
  groups = c("SNPS","RISK.ALLELE.FREQUENCY", "P.VALUE", "ORorBETA", "DISEASE.TRAIT"),
  data = curated_gwas_senses,
  type = "bubble",
  height = 650,
  width = 800

)
dP$xAxis(type = "addMeasureAxis", overrideMax = 1, outputFormat = ".2f")
dP$yAxis(overrideMax = 1, outputFormat = ".2f")
dP$legend(
   x = 200,
   y = 10,
   width = 400,
   height = 20,
   horizontalAlign = "right"
   )

dP$setTemplate(
  afterScript = sprintf(
'<script>
var line = d3.svg.line()
  .x(function(d) { return myChart.axes[0]._draw.scale()(d.x); })
  .y(function(d) { return myChart.axes[1]._draw.scale()(d.y); });

d3.select("#%s svg g")
  .append("path")
  .datum([{x:myChart.axes[0]._min,y:0},{x:myChart.axes[0]._max,y:1}])
  .attr("d",line)
  .style("stroke", "red")
  .style("stroke-width",0.5)
  .style("stroke-dasharray", "2");
</script>
',
dP$params$dom
))

dP$save('specificity-sensitivity_plot.html', cdn = TRUE)
cat('<a href=specificity-sensitivity_plot.html> specificity-sensitivity plot</a>')
